title.narrative: Children are protected from weather hazards through essential winter kits and blankets

description.narrative: Over 320,000 vulnerable children and their families were supported with in-kind and cash assistance to help them cope with the increased socio-economic hardship brought about by the winter seasons.These included104,452displaced children who received winter clothes to protect them from the harsh weather conditions (52 per cent girls); and 42,431 families (212,155 people with 108,143 children – 49 per cent girls) in urban and peri-urban areas who received a humanitarian cash transfers to help them mitigate the ongoing socio-economic hardship. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:16/01/2022
